They found her bag. I used to work for TSA. Here's how to never lose your bag. Forget the luggage tags. Those belt conveyors rip those off. I've seen a pile of them a foot high under a conveyor. Next. Take an 8 1/2 X 11 sheet of copy paper. Print or type in large letters your name, address, phone, cel, email address. Using Duct Tape, tape that to the inside of the kid of your suitcase. They will always find yours. Take some crazy fabric, and make a bow. Tie that on your bag. When it comes to the baggage claim, you find it easier.
